A resolution was published on renaming Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky and a number of villages

04 Nov 2019, 13:10


The parliamentary publication Voice of Ukraine published a resolution on renaming the city of Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky and several villages.

This is stated in the edition of November 2.
"The Verkhovna Rada decides:
Rename the city of Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky Kiev region in the city of Pereyaslav;
Rename the village of Ostrovka Manevichsky district of the Volyn region in the village of Islands;
Rename the village of Rachki in the Nemirovsky District into the village of Podolsk;
Rename the village of Birki Sokalsky district of Lviv region in the village of Borok;
Rename the village of Mazarnya-Karanska of Kamenka-Bugsky district of the Lviv region to the village of Mazyarnya-Karanska. "
Recall that in the urban type city of Novgorod Donetsk region, which is subordinate to the Toretskaya military-civil administration, some of the residents spoke in favor of returning the historic name of New York to the town.

